[92:8]  But he who is stingy, though he is rich.

12
00:00:38,223 --> 00:00:40,223
[92:9]  And disbelieves in the scripture.

13
00:00:40,223 --> 00:00:42,223
[92:10]  We will direct him towards misery.

14
00:00:42,460 --> 00:00:45,500
[92:11]  His money cannot help him when he falls.

15
00:00:45,951 --> 00:00:47,670
[92:12]  We provide the guidance.

16
00:00:47,670 --> 00:00:50,248
[92:13]  We control the Hereafter, as well as this life.

17
00:00:50,949 --> 00:00:53,690
[92:14]  I have warned you about the blazing Hellfire.

18
00:00:54,191 --> 00:00:58,538
[92:15]  None burns therein except the wicked.
[92:16]  Who disbelieves and turns away.

19
00:00:59,039 --> 00:01:02,769
[92:17]  Avoiding it will be the righteous.
[92:18]  Who gives from his money to charity.

20
00:01:02,769 --> 00:01:07,140
[92:19]  Seeking nothing in return.
[92:20]  Seeking only his Lord, the Most High.

21
00:01:07,540 --> 00:01:09,655
[92:21]  He will certainly attain salvation.

22
00:01:13,061 --> 00:01:14,810
Verse 1 and verse 2.

23
00:01:14,810 --> 00:01:17,380
[92:1]  By the night as it covers.
[92:2]  The day as it reveals.

24
00:01:17,380 --> 00:01:22,359
There are many, many verses which refer to
day, night, forenoon, and dawn.

25
00:01:24,162 --> 00:01:28,023
The night is created for our rest and therefore
is a benefit.

26
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:40,000
And we can use that as an analogy to this life because we're blocked from being in God's presence while we're in this life.

27
00:01:40,382 --> 00:01:43,331
It is a sort of darkness. It is a sort of barrier.

28
00:01:43,331 --> 00:01:46,641
We cannot stand God's presence in our present
form.

29
00:01:47,979 --> 00:01:50,000
[92:2]  The day as it reveals.

30
00:01:51,442 --> 00:01:58,821
Most of the references in Quran about day
are about the Day of Resurrection all the way through.

31
00:01:59,620 --> 00:02:06,060
And I thought of that as an analogy to life
which reveals the truth and things as they are.

32
00:02:06,359 --> 00:02:11,179
And I thought that appropriate too, when we consider
the Day of Resurrection, the Day of Judgment,

33
00:02:11,179 --> 00:02:13,330
because that's, in fact, what will happen.

34
00:02:13,831 --> 00:02:20,000
We're all familiar with this night and how black
it can be without any stars or the moon out.

35
00:02:20,541 --> 00:02:25,874
I used to live up on a hill in the middle
of the country and there was no electricity from house to house.

36
00:02:26,290 --> 00:02:29,240
There's nothing to see except the lightning
bugs if you were fortunate.

37
00:02:29,641 --> 00:02:31,891
You couldn't see your hand in front of your
face.

38
00:02:31,891 --> 00:02:32,956
It was that dark.

39
00:02:33,658 --> 00:02:34,954
And that's quite a cover.

40
00:02:34,954 --> 00:02:41,948
It removes our world from us so that what
we remember of the world in the daylight really is an illusion.

41
00:02:42,387 --> 00:02:48,636
The night takes everything away and that's
what happened to us when we had to come to this life.

42
00:02:48,636 --> 00:02:53,642
We had to be away from our real life for the
period of time we're here.

43
00:02:54,315 --> 00:02:59,794
And when the sun comes up and things begin
to take shape, the first thing that we see is silhouettes usually.

44
00:02:59,794 --> 00:03:05,614
I live across the street from a park now and
when the sun rises, the trees don't have any texture or depth of color.

45
00:03:05,614 --> 00:03:08,179
They're shapes as the sun begins to come up.

46
00:03:08,580 --> 00:03:09,800
And they look flat.

47
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:19,216
And as the sun rises further, the color appears and then its depth and texture and you see individual leaves moving and all the parts that make up the tree.

48
00:03:19,591 --> 00:03:25,978
And so the day is revelation and the Day of
Judgment is a revelation to all of us,

49
00:03:25,978 --> 00:03:30,409
even those of us who hope to be safe on the
Day of Resurrection.

50
00:03:30,759 --> 00:03:34,773
I think we will also see things that we did
not see ever in this lifetime.

51
00:03:36,773 --> 00:03:42,079
[92:3]  And Him who created the male and the female.
[92:4]  Your works are of various kinds.

52
00:03:43,632 --> 00:03:50,691
Some time ago, I went through Quran and looked
for all of the references that God made to the human being,

53
00:03:50,691 --> 00:03:54,194
whether it was about creation or about our
nature and our characters.

54
00:03:54,495 --> 00:04:01,103
And there are an awful lot, as I was telling
Lydia before we started, an awful lot of descriptions of us

55
00:04:01,103 --> 00:04:11,569
that are not real positive. We're hasty, we're unappreciative, contentious, parsimonious,

56
00:04:11,569 --> 00:04:14,421
and unappreciative is throughout quite a bit.

57
00:04:14,621 --> 00:04:21,780
And there are rare instances where the verse might finish with the phrase "except for those who lead a righteous life" or something similar.

58
00:04:22,604 --> 00:04:31,243
Our works are of various kinds. And for those of us who do things that appear to be Quranic but we are still involved in idol worship,

59
00:04:31,243 --> 00:04:36,649
we know that those works are nullified. And
in fact, God designs those works to help others.

60
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:44,610
We are all in the service of each other but that on the Day of Resurrection, if we are involved in idol worship, they will be as if we had not done them.

61
00:04:48,868 --> 00:04:56,779
Verses 5 through 11 describe two types of
people.

62
00:04:57,681 --> 00:05:01,034
God alone knows what each of our choice was,

63
00:05:01,034 --> 00:05:05,589
what in our hearts we really believe even though
we forgot when we came here.

64
00:05:06,941 --> 00:05:16,655
For those of us who chose God alone, God willing all of us, God will give us everything in our life to augment that choice.

65
00:05:17,807 --> 00:05:19,807
We know those things as tests.

66
00:05:19,807 --> 00:05:23,861
We know them as gifts. We know them as miracles. We each have stories to tell.

67
00:05:24,663 --> 00:05:33,676
And as we recognize them as such, they augment and cement and increase our faith and our knowledge in God's truth and His guarantees.

68
00:05:34,528 --> 00:05:42,539
For those who do not believe, God also provides
for them what they need to continue disbelief.

69
00:05:43,491 --> 00:05:47,695
It may appear as though they're wondrous
things for instance they're very wealthy or people

70
00:05:47,695 --> 00:05:53,201
that have great status or people that seem
to have a lot of power and can get people

71
00:05:53,201 --> 00:05:56,002
in countries to do things for themselves, for
instance.

72
00:05:56,453 --> 00:06:00,958
Those people may consider themselves blessed,
but God is merely continuing to test them

73
00:06:00,958 --> 00:06:05,563
so that at the end, at the Day of Judgment,
there will be no excuse whatsoever.

74
00:06:05,563 --> 00:06:11,620
Nothing they can say or do except to ask to come back and try again which, of course, we know will not be allowed.

75
00:06:12,221 --> 00:06:18,128
So, I read those verses as descriptions of
how God is so Merciful to all of us

76
00:06:18,128 --> 00:06:23,735
because even though God knows the choice of the disbelievers
and augments that choice in their life,

77
00:06:23,735 --> 00:06:28,991
He still is providing proof of God alone and
the truth to them

78
00:06:28,991 --> 00:06:33,982
in the midst of all the things that are given and all the things that
seem to be provided so easily.

79
00:06:37,448 --> 00:06:43,377
What I thought was that I constantly think
that this life is an illusion it is one huge test

80
00:06:43,377 --> 00:06:54,216
for all of us, believers or not, and we have to keep striving to find the truth to be believers with certainty and that's very difficult.

81
00:06:56,034 --> 00:06:59,314
Sometimes some of the things that God causes
to happen in our lives,

82
00:06:59,314 --> 00:07:06,223
the people we meet, the settings we find ourselves in are confusing
and they can make us wonder if we're on the right path at all.

83
00:07:06,223 --> 00:07:10,219
But that is in fact the
test that we have to keep striving and stay

84
00:07:10,219 --> 00:07:17,664
right where we're going toward God alone and
whatever is puzzling will become clear very quickly if we do that.

85
00:07:18,926 --> 00:07:24,318
Does anybody have any comments, questions,
additions, up till here?

86
00:07:31,130 --> 00:07:31,978
Okay.

87
00:07:34,833 --> 00:07:36,282
[92:12]  We provide the guidance.

88
00:07:36,282 --> 00:07:38,933
[92:13]  We control the Hereafter, as well as this life.

89
00:07:40,417 --> 00:07:42,345
God controls all things.

90
00:07:42,896 --> 00:07:51,568
We speak of the words we utter, we think that they're our own, we think that the thoughts that we have are our own and we know that they aren't.

91
00:07:53,860 --> 00:07:58,532
God knows ahead of time what we're going to
say and the effect that our words are going to have on other people.

92
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:05,992
More than that

93
00:08:05,992 --> 00:08:08,543
[92:13]  We control the Hereafter, as well as this life.

94
00:08:08,543 --> 00:08:11,103
Our lives are so perfectly designed.

95
00:08:11,654 --> 00:08:14,606
We have all the choices in the world available
to us.

96
00:08:14,606 --> 00:08:19,211
What time we're going to get up for Salat
in the morning, we choose that time

97
00:08:19,211 --> 00:08:23,615
unless we wake up and don't need an alarm clock anymore
like Rashad.

98
00:08:25,615 --> 00:08:28,717
We choose what we're gonna have for breakfast
whether we're gonna eat at all.

99
00:08:29,118 --> 00:08:33,372
We choose how we're gonna get to work, we
choose what time, we choose what we're going

100
00:08:33,372 --> 00:08:37,977
to do when we get there, we choose how to prioritize
the tasks in a day we think,

101
00:08:37,977 --> 00:08:44,485
we have an awful lot of control over our lives, what we're going
to wear, what we're going to do when we come home

102
00:08:44,485 --> 00:08:49,190
that night, we make plans with the people
in our lives, relatives, friends.

103
00:08:50,392 --> 00:08:55,297
All of that is designed for us. We have no choice at all
in reality.

104
00:08:55,798 --> 00:09:02,206
All of that is a test and it's designed specifically,
individually for each person in the world.

105
00:09:04,206 --> 00:09:08,260
The money we earn is already predetermined.
To worry about it is foolish.

106
00:09:09,362 --> 00:09:14,367
We know that God is Merciful and provides
relief in every situation

107
00:09:14,367 --> 00:09:20,000
including the amount of money that we need. And all of us have stories about some great need arising and not having

108
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:23,753
the faintest idea in the world how we were
going to accomplish it, and

109
00:09:23,753 --> 00:09:26,504
suddenly, there was money from somewhere unexplained.

110
00:09:27,606 --> 00:09:34,264
Our relatives, those people that are part of our family, mother, father, aunts, uncles, cousins, they were chosen for us also.

111
00:09:35,116 --> 00:09:42,175
For some of us, we are distanced from our family
because of our choice to believe in God alone,

112
00:09:42,175 --> 00:09:47,882
but that's also part of our test. We were assigned
to their household as our children were assigned to our own.

113
00:09:48,433 --> 00:09:57,095
Those people that become friends of ours, those people that we find ourselves working with, whether we like them or not, were put there by God for us.

114
00:09:58,047 --> 00:10:03,603
I've talked before about working in a hospital
and part of my job is to take care of patients.

115
00:10:03,603 --> 00:10:09,460
They're assigned a person like myself when
they come into the hospital and we think that somebody

116
00:10:09,460 --> 00:10:15,395
there assigns Joe Smith to Catherine,
in fact God does that and allows me to meet

117
00:10:15,395 --> 00:10:19,102
some people and not others that come through
the hospital for a reason.

118
00:10:20,988 --> 00:10:26,585
Material things that we gain or do not gain
are again designed by God

119
00:10:26,585 --> 00:10:35,366
to test whether we're focused on the need for those or not, amongst other things the environmental settings that we find ourselves in.

120
00:10:37,088 --> 00:10:41,667
I remember traveling to the conference and
Rashad telling that story about the bugs

121
00:10:41,667 --> 00:10:46,160
at that time that we stopped to make Salat
and made it the fastest we'd ever made it before.

122
00:10:46,709 --> 00:10:50,793
All of us were destined to do that. We didn't
know that. We didn't know that was going to happen.

123
00:10:51,995 --> 00:10:55,449
And it was on green grass, as I remember,
in the middle of the desert.

124
00:10:55,449 --> 00:11:00,398
It was a nice carpet of grass and Rashad was right where there was no grass. He just seemed to be waiting for all of us.

125
00:11:00,749 --> 00:11:01,847
He certainly was.

126
00:11:03,731 --> 00:11:07,964
But for some reason all of us were to share
that experience and run

127
00:11:07,964 --> 00:11:12,318
back to the van, I remember going back to the van. We didn't stay there very long.

128
00:11:13,520 --> 00:11:19,527
All the things that are designed in our lives whether they're people or things or places we travel to, they're all designed

129
00:11:19,527 --> 00:11:25,434
by God. And in all of them is the proof of
God alone and that God controls all things.

130
00:11:25,885 --> 00:11:34,196
If we are truly searching for that, we'll see that in all things, in all conversations, in all the people that we meet, all the places that we go.

131
00:11:36,701 --> 00:11:40,554
If we know that God controls everything and
there are layers and layers of that.

132
00:11:40,554 --> 00:11:45,960
When we first begin to understand that God controls
everything, it's confusing

133
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:52,468
because you wanna say "well, wait a minute, I, I chose that and
I chose this" and, and then, the realization comes

134
00:11:52,468 --> 00:11:59,728
that God controls everything and you didn't choose it. But you still retain the thought that what's in your head is your own.

135
00:12:00,228 --> 00:12:02,829
Out there is ok, God's running all of that,

136
00:12:02,829 --> 00:12:08,085
but your thoughts are your own and you're using your mind to
understand that and then the next layer peels away

137
00:12:08,085 --> 00:12:11,237
and you realize that the thoughts you
have in your head are not even your own.

138
00:12:11,237 --> 00:12:16,343
They're part of a perfectly designed life for each
of us. And in those lives, the truth is buried

139
00:12:16,343 --> 00:12:21,549
everywhere. In fact, it's not buried, it's so
obvious and the more layers we peel away and

140
00:12:21,549 --> 00:12:25,953
the more understanding we come to have about
the reason we're here and what God is doing

141
00:12:25,953 --> 00:12:31,209
for us in His Great Mercy and Graciousness
to us, it becomes as if everything floats to

142
00:12:31,209 --> 00:12:34,010
the surface. The world looks very very different.

143
00:12:34,311 --> 00:12:37,263
Jason just bought a car and I was telling Rashad

144
00:12:37,263 --> 00:12:43,070
this the other day, he had to buy it
because it had a big 19 all over it but that's another story.

145
00:12:43,070 --> 00:12:46,422
And we were talking about him
driving on the road with him being just 16,

146
00:12:46,422 --> 00:12:52,429
his mother saying to myself "I really hope God
means it when He says He's gonna protect everybody" from Jason.

147
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:56,232
And we were talking, and we were talking and I said

148
00:12:56,232 --> 00:13:02,289
"you know, I often drive to work and I think of all of the things, the creatures that are driving along with me."

149
00:13:02,539 --> 00:13:10,000
It's not just the cars as bumper to bumper, but it's every person
in every car has a jinn riding with them

150
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:15,156
and two angels one on the right and one on the
left, and it's a wonder there's any room on the road for the car,

151
00:13:15,156 --> 00:13:20,763
when you think about that, but all those other people driving along looking right and left as if they don't know that.

152
00:13:21,013 --> 00:13:27,521
They've no idea how much protection is involved in those near misses when somebody turns left and we can see the angel right there.

153
00:13:27,739 --> 00:13:31,881
We can't, but we can, we know the angel
was there to avoid this crash.

154
00:13:32,232 --> 00:13:37,388
So, world takes on a very different perspective and, Alhamdu Lillah, a great peace occurs

155
00:13:37,388 --> 00:13:42,894
when we understand that what seems bad is in that
God is after us in Mercy

156
00:13:42,894 --> 00:13:50,354
and to provide the guidance that we need to find Him and return
to Him and never be separated again it's really incredible.

157
00:13:51,260 --> 00:13:54,324
A woman: Are there any comments about those
two verses?

158
00:13:56,778 --> 00:13:58,027
Dr. Khalifa: Finish the Sura.

159
00:13:58,027 --> 00:13:58,875
A woman: No.

160
00:14:00,428 --> 00:14:01,627
Dr. Khalifa: You're doing so well.

161
00:14:01,627 --> 00:14:03,627
A woman: Rashad, you have any comments at all?

162
00:14:03,627 --> 00:14:04,625
Dr. Khalifa: You finished.

163
00:14:04,625 --> 00:14:05,323
A woman: Yes.

164
00:14:06,116 --> 00:14:07,042
A woman: Ok.

165
00:14:07,543 --> 00:14:11,847
[92:14]  I have warned you about the blazing Hellfire.
[92:15]  None burns therein except the wicked.

166
00:14:11,847 --> 00:14:14,198
[92:16]  Who disbelieves and turns away.

167
00:14:14,699 --> 00:14:20,857
That's very straight forward. God gives many descriptions in Quran about the types of people that are going to end up in Hell.

168
00:14:22,244 --> 00:14:28,008
And some of them are almost abstract.
This is very straight forward and it's a bottom line.

169
00:14:28,260 --> 00:14:32,529
People who disbelieve and turn away are
wicked and there is no second chance.

170
00:14:32,980 --> 00:14:39,087
Hell is where these people will be and they don't
know it. They won't know it until the Day of Resurrection.

171
00:14:41,842 --> 00:14:43,842
[92:17]  Avoiding it will be the righteous.

172
00:14:43,842 --> 00:14:46,794
[92:18]  Who gives from his money to charity.
[92:19]  Seeking nothing in return.

173
00:14:46,794 --> 00:14:48,794
[92:20]  ... only his Lord, the Most High.

174
00:14:49,195 --> 00:14:51,195
[92:21]  He will certainly attain salvation.

175
00:14:51,195 --> 00:14:56,150
The righteous are spared with the greatest mercy because
we know that we've all sinned.

176
00:14:56,851 --> 00:15:06,014
For those of us who mercifully come to understand God alone and
free ourselves from any type of idol worship including our own ego,

177
00:15:06,014 --> 00:15:14,225
this is a tremendous accomplishment. It's described as such with words in Quran but I don't think we can fully understand

178
00:15:14,225 --> 00:15:23,739
how much mercy from God is involved here for us to escape even to end up in Purgatory hanging on by our toenails would be an incredible mercy.

179
00:15:25,380 --> 00:15:32,766
And then, God again very simply describes
those people who are going to avoid Hell for all eternity

180
00:15:32,766 --> 00:15:39,775
and those are people who are not really attached to this world, who understand that what is part of their life

181
00:15:39,775 --> 00:15:42,877
is, is given. It is all a gift from God.

182
00:15:43,127 --> 00:15:50,286
And it is not meant that we should keep every single thing that
comes our way and to think of anything as ours

183
00:15:50,286 --> 00:15:57,095
is also foolish because it's God's. And if we're meant to give it away then we should do that without ever looking back.

184
00:15:57,396 --> 00:16:05,657
One of the difficulties I had in my family being raised as a Christian, we had to go through that Christmas fantasy that happens for months every year.

185
00:16:06,110 --> 00:16:11,593
And in my family from the time I was very
young, the giving of gifts never was the giving of gifts,

186
00:16:11,593 --> 00:16:16,448
it was always attached to conditions
even though everyone knew, for instance, that

187
00:16:16,448 --> 00:16:20,702
we had three small children and didn't have
a lot of money and the gifts were given with

188
00:16:20,702 --> 00:16:26,659
great smiles, there was always the great frown
and the comments that similar gifts were not given in return.

189
00:16:27,565 --> 00:16:33,279
And if they weren't, it was
remembered from year to year to year to year, forever.

190
00:16:33,580 --> 00:16:38,085
And finally, long before I moved to
Tucson, Alhamdu Lillah, I just told my family

191
00:16:38,085 --> 00:16:42,840
"we don't do Christmas anymore. I don't know what
it is anymore. I don't know what you think you're doing,

192
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:46,443
"but I cannot participate in it. I cannot encourage my children to do this."

193
00:16:46,994 --> 00:16:51,603
This is, this is just horrible. You don't know how to
give anything. My family would come to help,

194
00:16:51,603 --> 00:16:56,411
and the help was more of a burden because
