00:36:52,758 --> 00:37:00,000
Be careful how we speak of God. It came to mind
because Rashad talked to us one day about

435
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:02,351
being careful how we spoke about God.

436
00:37:02,351 --> 00:37:03,900
God does not make us sick.

437
00:37:04,416 --> 00:37:06,567
We make ourselves sick. God heals.

438
00:37:08,567 --> 00:37:11,769
We used, I think you used this example of Moses
and his teacher.

439
00:37:11,769 --> 00:37:18,127
And each one of those examples, it was the
human being that made the error and God that made it right.

440
00:37:18,878 --> 00:37:21,479
So, we need to proclaim God's blessing to us.

441
00:37:21,479 --> 00:37:26,234
We don't need to say to each other "well, God
made that tire flat" and leave it there.

442
00:37:26,234 --> 00:37:31,790
We need to understand what we're saying. We need to be real careful. If the tire's flat, we did something.

443
00:37:32,341 --> 00:37:35,443
God will help us get the tire fixed so the
car will go again.

444
00:37:36,345 --> 00:37:40,000
